Pharmacy, Dispensing and Responsibility

Adam La Caze

March 2022

Objectives

  1. Appreciate, and start to develop the attitudes of a pharmacist, especially with respect to dispensing
  2. Develop a systematic process to dispensing

Discussion

UQwordcloud

What is the role of the pharmacist?

What feedback do preceptors give about students and interns?

Key concepts

  1. Pharmacists take responsibility for getting dispensing right
  2. The overall aim is always improving patient outcomes
  3. The challenge of dispensing is always and efficiently ensuring a rather long list of easy things are done correctly and well (while not losing sight that the objective is to improve patient outcomes)

Examples

  • It is late Saturday afternoon, Jonathan has just been discharged from the local hospital following a knee replacement. He has a discharge script for his pain medicines, but no script for his anticonvulsant. You cant get in touch with the hospital doctor or his usual GP.

Examples

A mans daughter comes to the pharmacy with a prescription for methotrexate 2.5mg, 30.

The directions were to take 2 daily for a psoriasis flare up.
